documentation.text:
@dev Updates the KYC request (Either Approves or Rejects)
 @return User object which contains the role & other basic info

devdoc.author: Suresh Konakanchi
devdoc.details: Library for managing KYC process seemlessly using de-centralised system

actionOnKycRequest(address,bool,string).details: Updates the KYC request (Either Approves or Rejects)

params.approve_: Approve the data hash or reject
params.note_: Any info that need to be shared

params.makeActive_: If true, bank will be marked as active, else, it will be marked as deactivateds

params.bank_: Bank details, which need to be added to the system

params.currentTime_: Current Date & Time in unix epoch timestamp
params.customer_: Customer details for whom the request is to be raised
params.notes_: Any additional notes that need to be added

getAllBanks(uint256).details: All the banks list. Data will be sent in pages to avoid the more gas fee

params.pageNumber: page number for which data is needed (1..2..3....n)

returns._1: Bank[] List of banks in the current page

getBankDetails(address).details: To get details of the bank

returns._0: Bank object which will have complete details of the bank

getBankRequests(uint256).details: This is customer facing RPC end point

params.pageNumber: page number for which data is needed (1..2..3....n)

returns._1: KycRequest[] List of KYC requests in the current page

getCustomerDetails(address).details: To get details of the customer

returns._0: Customer object which will have complete details of the customer

getCustomersOfBank(uint256).details: List of customers, who are linked to the current bank. Data will be sent in pages to avoid the more gas fee

params.pageNumber: page number for which data is needed (1..2..3....n)

returns._1: KycRequest[] List of KYC requests in the current page

params.id_: Customer ID for whom the request has to be re-raised
params.notes_: Any additional notes that need to be added

removerDatahashPermission(address,string.details: Removes the permission to a specific bank, so that they can't access the documents again

params.bankId_: Id of the bank to whom permission has to be revoked
params.notes_: Any additional notes that need to included

searchBanks(address).details: Search for bank details in the list that the customer is directly linked to

returns._0: boolean to say if bank exists or not
returns._1: Bank object to get the complete details of the bank
returns._2: KycRequest object to get the details about the request & it's status Costly operation if we had more banks linked to this single customer

searchCustomers(address).details: Search for customer details in the list that the bank is directly linked to

returns._0: boolean to say if customer exists or not
returns._1: Customer object to get the complete details of the customer
returns._2: KycRequest object to get the details about the request & it's status Costly operation if we had more customers linked to this single bank

params.email_: Bank's email address that need to be updated
params.name_: Bank's name which need to be updated

updateDatahash(string,uint256).details: Updates the Datahash of the documents

params.currentTime_: Current Date Time in unix epoch timestamp
params.hash_: Data hash value that need to be updated

updateKycVerification(address,bool,strin.details: To mark the KYC verification as failure

params.note_: Any info that need to be shared

params.email_: Email that need to be updated
params.mobile_: Mobile number that need to be updated

whoAmI().details: Updates the KYC request (Either Approves or Rejects)

returns._0: User object which contains the role & other basic info
